Description. Male (UFAM, paratype ):
Prosoma brown, pale brown medially, with brown margins and brown fovea. Eye borders black. Chelicerae brown with faint darker brown longitudinal stripe. Legs and pedipalps yellowish brown (
Fig. 13
). Sternum pale orange with brown margins. Labium and endites pale orange, distally yellow. Opisthosoma brown with dorsal pattern of densely arranged cream colored marks (
Fig. 13
). Total length 3.5 . Prosoma: 1.6 long, 1.4 wide. Opisthosoma: 1.8 long, 1.0 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.14 , 0.12 , 0.10 , 0.10 ; interdistances: 0.08 , 0.04 , 0.12 , 0.10 , 0.10 , 0.02 . Legs: I: 6.3 ( 1.7 , 0.7 , 1.9 , 1.5 , 0.5 ); II: 6.4 ( 1.9 , 0.7 , 1.8 , 1.5 , 0.5 ); III: 5.2 ( 1.6 , 0.6 , 1.2 , 1.4 , 0.4 ); IV: 6.8 ( 1.8 , 0.6 , 1.6 , 2.0, 0.8 ). Spination: femur I p 1 - 1 -0 r 1 - 1 -0; tibiae I–II
v 6
pairs. Palp: tibia with one prolateral spine; dRTA conical, three times longer than vRTA; VTA small, slightly retrolateral; cymbium more than two times tibia length with retrolateral grove, flanked by strong setae; tegulum/subtegulum notch at 3 o’clock; tegulum flanked prolaterally by hyaline lamina, protruding slightly at the base of embolus and more developed at the base of conductor; embolus long and slender, arising at 5 o’clock (
Figs 53–54
).

Female (IBSP 137207 , paratype ):
Prosoma pale brown with brown eye area, brown margins and brown Ushaped pattern extending from cephalic region to posterior margin of prosoma. Chelicerae brown with pair of dark brown longitudinal stripes. Legs and pedipalps pale brown, legs with brown bands (
Fig. 14
). Sternum pale orange with brown margins. Labium and endites pale orange, distally yellow. Opisthosoma cream colored with brown scattered marks (
Fig. 14
). Total length 5.3 . Prosoma: 1.9 long, 1.6 wide. Opisthosoma: 3.2 long, 1.7 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.14 , 0.12 , 0.10 , 0.12 ; interdistances: 0.10 , 0.02 , 0.12 , 0.08 , 0.08 , 0.06 . Legs: I: 6.2 ( 1.6 , 0.7 , 1.9 , 1.5 , 0.5 ); II: 6.4 ( 1.8 , 0.7 , 1.9 , 1.5 , 0.5 ); III: 5.3 ( 1.5 , 0.6 , 1.2 , 1.5 , 0.5 ); IV: 6.2 ( 1.6 , 0.6 , 1.5 , 1.9 , 0.6 ). Spination: femur I: p 1 - 1 -0; r 1 - 1 -0; tibiae I–II: 8 pairs; tibia III: p0, r0. Epigyne: epigynal field two times wider than long; lateral lobes with small, posterior triangular projections, not reaching in height the posterior margin of the median septum; median septum almost two times longer than wide, posteriorly convex (
Fig. 55
). Vulva: Cp long and strongly convoluted; fertilization ducts short, thick and pointing away from each other (
Fig. 56
).

Distribution. Brazil (states of Amazonas, Pará and Amapá) (
Fig. 59
).
